header.gameNote: PHILLIPS 66 BIG 12 WOMEN'S CHAMPIONSHIP - 1st ROUND AT KANSAS CITY MO

article.description: Brittainey Raven scored 11 points and Texas (No. 20 ESPN/USA Today, No. 15 AP) held off Missouri 64-59 in the first round of the Big 12 women's tournament Thursday.
article.headline: Texas puts away Missouri in final minute to advance to Big 12 quarters
article.linkText: No. 20 Texas survives Mizzou in Big 12 tourney
article.story:
KANSAS CITY, Mo. -- Brittainey Raven scored 11 points and Texas (No. 20 ESPN/USA Today, No. 15 AP) held off Missouri 64-59 in the first round of the Big 12 women's tournament Thursday.

Fifth-seeded Texas (23-7) trailed 29-28 at the half and couldn't put away the Tigers until the final minute. The Longhorns advanced to a quarterfinal game Friday against fourth-seeded Texas A&M.

Missouri (12-18) lost in its final game under Cindy Stein, who announced her resignation March 1. Stein was 185-177 in 12 years at Mizzou.

Amanda Hanneman kept the Tigers in the game, making a career-high seven 3-pointers and finishing with a game-high 21 points. Jessra Johnson had 11 points.
